      "narrative": {
        "News": "Slovakia - Slovnaft - Bratislava: the 55,000 bpd CDU was restarted during the evening of July 13 (GMT). Increased activity began at the unit on July 11 and the unit was shut on June 25. Earlier, the 16,000 bpd catalytic reformer was restarted during the evening of July 12. The 16,000 bpd naphtha hydrotreater was shut on July 3 and remained offline.",
        "Ongoing Events": "Hungary - MOL - Duna: the 21,100 bpd coker was shut during the evening of July 11 (GMT). The unit was recently restarted on July 10 after being shut on June 6. The 72,300 bpd CDU and the 74,000 bpd VDU were shut following a fire on October 20 and remained offline. Poland - Orlen - Plock: the 70,000 bpd hydrocracker and a hydrogen plant were restarted during the morning of July 1. Increased activity began at the units on June 25. The hydrocracker was shut on May 13 and the hydrogen plant was shut on May 15. Also, a 69,500 bpd CDU and a 51,000 bpd VDU were shut on June 27 and the 22,000 bpd visbreaker was shut on May 14. The units remained offline. Planned work was expected to begin mid-May, according to sources.",
        "Planned Maintenance": "Poland - Orlen - Plock: planned work on a hydrocracker was expected to begin mid-May, according to sources. Lithuania - Orlen Lietuva- Mazekai: unspecified planned work on a number of units is expected to start in Q1 and Q2. More maintenance is expected in 2027, according to sources."
